      <title>Re: What ever happened to Cleric Mana Regen?</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&amp;message.id=10723#M10723</link>
      <description>I think this is a real issue on raids, but trivial in groups.  Unless you're doing content WAY over your head (or don't have a tank appropriate for the content), then it's pretty tough for a smart cleric to go oom in xp groups.  Yah, CH in groups is a real yawner, but it gets the job done at a fairly minimal cost.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;On raids, however, the slow mana regen becomes more of an issue.  Clerics have it worse than any other pure caster because our self mana buff doesn't stack with Oak.  Chanters have gather, wizzies have familiars and gather, shammies have canni, necros have lich, mages can steal mana from pets and have mod rods (although those are shareable) and druids... well, druids are almost as bad off as clerics, except that they get the little bit extra from their self-buff.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;There actually was a gather mana AA for clerics in testing (for DoN, I think), but it never made it off of beta.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The real problem with giving clerics a huge mana regen boost is that it would wreck old content (including relatively recent old content), which is designed around old levels of mana regen.  So, what Sony needs to do is figure out a way to increase post-wipe regen without trivializing content.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I'm not a programmer, so I have no clue how tough some of these solutions would be to implement, but here are my suggestions:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;To deal with raid mana regen after wipes:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;(1)  a new raid leader AA that gives a raid 25%/50%/75% of it's mana back.  HOWEVER, this ability cannot be activated if anyone in the raid is in an raid level dynamic zone or task.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;(2)  a new raid leader AA that basically brings the guildhall hot tub to the raid, for increased hp/mana/end regen.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;(3)  an enchanter AA that summons a Ward which increases mana regen (can give the ward 1hp and make it generate insane aggro, if it's too powerful for use during encounters).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;To deal with cleric mana regen issues in general:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;(1)  make Armour of the XXX stack with the Oak line (maybe decrease the Armour line hps a bit at the same time).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;(2)  increase the FT cap by another 5-10 (for all classes).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;(3)  give clerics the mastery of the past AA (even though this wouldn't work on our high level spam heals, at least we'd stop fizzling CH, a level 39 spell that we've cast 100k+ times).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;(4)  give clerics a diety-specific familiar with benefits similar to wizzy familiars (I want a giant floating beer stein!)</description>
