      <title>Re: What ever happened to Cleric Mana Regen?</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&amp;message.id=10775#M10775</link>
      <description>&lt;BR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;HR&gt;&#xD;
&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Zamboni wrote:&lt;BR&gt;.&lt;BR&gt;There actually was a gather mana AA for clerics in testing (for DoN, I think), but it never made it off of beta.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;FONT color=#0000ff&gt;Both Druids and Clerics have posted similar ideas for a Gather Mana AA that has some kind of nastiness (like a 30s stun, etc.) which i think would be a good deal.&amp;nbsp; Generally raids wait for everyone to get FM, but w/out the Healers being Almost to Full Mana, your raid isn't gonna move.&amp;nbsp; I think the hardest part of their job is just balancing abilities like this that would be GREAT for raid's, but make it way too powerful to be used in group settings.&amp;nbsp; So maybe the Priest (and maybe casters in general) community needs to think about ways to help the Dev's thinking process along =)&amp;nbsp; I thought coder's were supposed to have good problem solving skills?&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;The real problem with giving clerics a huge mana regen boost is that it would wreck old content (including relatively recent old content), which is designed around old levels of mana regen. So, what Sony needs to do is figure out a way to increase post-wipe regen without trivializing content.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;To deal with raid mana regen after wipes:&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;(1) a new raid leader AA that gives a raid 25%/50%/75% of it's mana back. HOWEVER, this ability cannot be activated if anyone in the raid is in an raid level dynamic zone or task.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;FONT color=#0000ff&gt;Would be nice, but seems pretty hard to impliment (used to code in C++ for ackmuds.)&amp;nbsp; ALso, how helpful would it really be if it can't be activated in a Zone/Task?&amp;nbsp; ALmost&amp;nbsp;all end-game content is gotten by Task or Instance, and the time you really need the extra regen is after a wipe when everyone is rez'ing and rebuffing IN the zone you wiped in.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;(2) a new raid leader AA that basically brings the guildhall hot tub to the raid, for increased hp/mana/end regen.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT color=#0000ff&gt;Not a bad idea.&amp;nbsp; Hard to impliment just because you gotta come up with: Would it radiate out from the Raid Leader, how far would the radius be, how long would it last, agro effects of it, etc.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;BR&gt;(3) an enchanter AA that summons a Ward which increases mana regen (can give the ward 1hp and make it generate insane aggro, if it's too powerful for use during encounters).&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;Now this is a very nice original idea.&amp;nbsp; Would be great for all classes... Only prob i see it facing is how would you control it for group settings?&amp;nbsp; It some places the extra regen would make content super-trivial.&amp;nbsp; But then again, as levels are raised and new content comes out, older content should become even more trivial...&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT color=#0000ff&gt;Maybe an idea they could add to help this plus numerous other ideas is create some "Raid-Only" AAs, where you are required to be in a Raid to use them.&amp;nbsp; Also have it set so that if using any of the Raid-Only AA's, the abilities stop when you leave the raid.&amp;nbsp; Yes, i can already see that some can "cheat" or use a loophole to abuse it&amp;nbsp; (create a raid just to be able to use those AA's)... but maybe yall can help figure how to fix it.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;To deal with cleric mana regen issues in general:&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;(1) make Armour of the XXX stack with the Oak line (maybe decrease the Armour line hps a bit at the same time).&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;FONT color=#0000ff&gt;IMO (a druid one mind you), this should have been done long ago.&amp;nbsp; I think they should remove the HP component all-together, and make it stack with both CV and Bali.&amp;nbsp; That way you get your self-only mana regen buff that almost all caster class get some form of.&amp;nbsp; Only thing i dont like about it is that it bumps cleric Mana Regen up and leaves Druids in last :P&amp;nbsp; &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;(2) increase the FT cap by another 5-10 (for all classes).&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT color=#0000ff&gt;IMO, they should make an AA that you gotta get after the OOW AA's that removes the cap altogether.&amp;nbsp; Sounds a little overpowering at first....but what's the point of them adding FT to so many items and so many augs if it has such a low cap?&amp;nbsp; Plus the distribution of loot will have a balance on it.... the newer/younger players will likely have less AA's, less gear not much FT (prolly 10-20 total), while your end-game raiders are cap'd at 20, but wear 30+ Mana regen (in addition to having many augs in the bank that are deemed worthless because of the cap).&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;BR&gt;&lt;BR&gt;(3) give clerics the mastery of the past AA (even though this wouldn't work on our high level spam heals, at least we'd stop fizzling CH, a level 39 spell that we've cast 100k+ times).&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;FONT color=#0000ff&gt;SoE has been promising a fix to the fizzle-rate post 65, but haven't seen any word on it lately.&amp;nbsp; How much crap is it for a Level 70 &amp;lt;fill in your class&amp;gt; with 800 AAs, every possible AA to prevent Fizzle (including stupid stufflike Secondary Forte), yet STILL fizzle a spell 3 times in a row?&amp;nbsp; &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&#xD;
